	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Wed Jun 05, 2013 8:09 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: &quot;Street Fighter II&quot; for the NES theoretically possible?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Any &quot;real attempt&quot; would need Capcom's OK. Otherwise, it's still a bootleg.<br /><br />The concept of an NES fighting game comes up from time to time on NESdev BBS and in EFnet #nesdev. I ended up figuring out that a version with a scale of 4 cm = 1 pixel, or roughly 48 pixel tall characters, would probably be realistic for the NES without <em>too</em> much flicker. The hardest part of making an NES fighting game would be to find people willing to draw hundreds of frames of animation, roughly 120-160 for each original character, but then that might not be hard if we can enlist MUGEN fans in this effort.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


