	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Or have it contextually determine whether a punch or kick is appropriate based on the directions + A and the character's fighting style. One popular two-button fighter has this system:<br /><br /><strong>On ground</strong><br /><ul><li>A: Jab </li><li>Forward+wait+A: Strong </li><li>Down+wait+A: Low </li><li>Forward+A: Fierce </li><li>Down+A: Sweep </li><li>Up+A: High </li></ul><br /><strong>In air</strong><br /><ul><li>A: Spin </li><li>Up+A, Down+A, Left+A, Right+A: Strong attack in that direction </li></ul><br />This frees up B and directions+B for the special moves.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


